South Africa’s largest city is used to dealing with national power outages that snarl traffic and cause delays due to operational issues at state-owned utility Eskom. Now Johannesburg’s electricity company has been targeted by hackers. #Update City Power has been hit by a Ransomware virus. it has encrypted all our databases, applications and network. Currently our ICT department is cleaning and rebuilding all impacted applications.^GR — @CityPowerJhb (@CityPowerJhb) July 25, 2019  Businesses and families in the nation’s commercial hub can be thankful for one thing: The lights are still on. © 2019 Bloomberg L.P.